Le paragraphe 6 est en : FRA
	Post Description 

==========================================
Le paragraphe 7 est en : ENG
	We are currently looking for a bioinformatician familiar
with the computing infrastructure used for Illumina HiSeq sequencing and
sequencing data quality control. The Genomics Unit
(http://www.crg.es/genomics_unit) provides service to clients from within the
CRG/PRBB, as well as to external users. The Unit has established workflows for
many different types of high-throughput sequencing projects, including genomic sequencing,
mRNA-Seq, and ChIP-Seq, and is equipped with two Illumina HiSeq sequencing
instruments. Additional instrument purchases are foreseen as new technologies
become available.

==========================================
Le paragraphe 8 est en : ENG
	Main responsibilities 

==========================================
Le paragraphe 9 est en : ENG
	Specific tasks of the position in the context of
sequencing data production bioinformatics will include: 
Quality control of sequencing runs using established
pipelines; development and implementation of new workflows for data quality
control and data interpretation; LIMS (laboratory information managment
system)-based run management; Illumina software upgrades and maintenance of
data archive; making sequencing data and run reports available to users of the
Unit. 
Aside from that, the candidate will analyse data from technology
implementation projects and experimental sequencing runs. 

==========================================
Le paragraphe 10 est en : FRA
	Candidate requirements 

==========================================
Le paragraphe 11 est en : ENG
	Experience:
Experience in handling and analysing Illumina data and
Proficiency with a scripting language such as Perl experienced in using R for
data analysis. 
Experience with managing databases and LIMS systems is
essential. 
Knowledge in molecular biology and/or molecular genetics
is desirable. The post requires a client-oriented attitude, as well as an
interest for scientific questions that can be addressed using novel high-throughput
sequencing technologies.

==========================================
Le paragraphe 12 est en : ENG
	Degree:
Master’s degree or Ph.D. in computer sciences,
bioinformatics, biostatistics or related discipline. 

==========================================
Le paragraphe 13 est en : ENG
	Language:
Fluent in English.

==========================================
Le paragraphe 14 est en : ENG
	Personality: 
• Highly motivated candidate with interactive personality
who shows independent work performance. 
• Analytical skills and critical thinking

==========================================
Le paragraphe 15 est en : ENG
	Conditions
• Estimated annual gross salary: 
A competitive salary will be provided, which will be well
matched relative to the cost of living in Barcelona, and adjusted according to
experience.
• Starting date: February, 2014

